[src:collision-detection-2d/hyperplane-separation-theorem] Now by the second case, for each pair $A_{k},B_{k}$ there exists some unit vector $v_{k}$ and real number $c_{k}$ , such that $\langle v_{k},A_{k}\rangle <c_{k}<\langle v_{k},B_{k}\rangle$ .
[src:collision-detection-2d/hyperplane-separation-theorem] Since the unit sphere is compact, we can take a convergent subsequence, so that $v_{k}\to v$ .
